  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Teach and Equip 10 Afghan Widows to be Tailors</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghan widows with children usually face a very hard life.  Often, their children must beg in the streets rather than attend school.  But there are relatively good economic prospects for a woman trained as a tailor.  We will provide an expert teacher (herself a widow,) sewing machines, all the tools and even childcare, so that at the end of the yearlong course, the 10 women will have everything they need to start their own home tailoring businesses and support their families.</narrative>
  </description>
